				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">hello all.. i am having a problem with lighting/shadows in a q2 map i'm working on.. i've removed all the lights from it and only left the textures that emit light..
<br />

<br />
i am using the map compile tools that are provided on this page: <a href="http://home.insightbb.com/~gryndehl/q2compile/quake2.html" target="_blank" class="postlink">http://home.insightbb.com/~gryndehl/q2compile/quake2.html</a>
<br />

<br />
here is an image of my problem.. without regular lighting, on the right circle, you can see a shadow in the indention in the floor by the wall whereas, you don't see that shadow circled on the left side.. with regular lighting in place, that shadow becomes a bright area.. it happens to both floor indentions on the right side and on both sides of the indention..
<br />

<br />
i've tried redoing all the brushes on that side and it produces the same effect.. i know the problem is very minor but damn my perfectionism.. =P
<br />

<br />
<img src="http://aphrodite.deafening-urge.net/~scorpz/images/lightprob.jpg" border="0" /></span><span class=sign></span><span class="gensmall"></span>
